I've hardened `src/lib/run-agent.ts` with a 90s timeout wrapper, graceful Anthropic-error handling (audit log + status=failed, no throw), and an idempotency guard that skips re-running an agent if a `running`/`completed` row already exists for that `(payload_id, role)`. I also added `src/check-live-smoke.ts`, wired up `npm run check:smoke`, and added the `SMOKE_TEST_ORG_ID`/`SMOKE_TEST_PAYLOAD_ID` vars to `.env.example` (`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` was already present there). Typecheck and the secret scan are both clean. I'm now waiting on the full `check:agents` regression suite to finish before committing, merging to main, and pushing.
